messages.content: What is the smallest country in the world?

message.content:
The smallest country in the world is officially Vatican City, with an area of approximately 0.44 km² (0.17 sq mi). It is located within Rome, Italy, and is home to the Pope and the central government of the Catholic Church.

Vatican City has a population of around 800 people, making it the smallest internationally recognized sovereign state in the world, both by area and population. Despite its small size, Vatican City has its own government, currency, postal system, and even its own police force.

Interestingly, Vatican City is also the headquarters of the Catholic Church and is home to numerous iconic landmarks, including St. Peter's Basilica, the Sistine Chapel, and the Vatican Museums.
